<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Literary_theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Carroll, J. (2007). Evolutionary Approaches to Literature and Drama. In Robin Dunbar and Louise Barrett, (Eds.), <i>The Oxford Handbook of Evolutionary Psychology</i>. Chapter 44. <a href="http://www.umsl.edu/~engjcarr/web_documents/Ev%20Approaches%20to%20Lit%20&amp;%20%20Drama%20%28Oxford%20handbook%29.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.umsl.edu/~engjcarr/web_documents/Ev%20Approaches%20to%20Lit%20&amp;%20%20Drama%20%28Oxford%20handbook%29.htm" rel="nofollow">Full text</a></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Castle, Gregory. <i>Blackwell Guide to Literary Theory</i>. Malden, MA: Blackwell Publishing, 2007.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jonathan_Culler" title="Jonathan Culler">Culler, Jonathan.</a> <i>The Literary in Theory</i>. Stanford: Stanford University Press, 2007.</li>
</ul>


